Japanese Bought Net 118.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-07-06T23:56:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/japanese-bought-net-118-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 1 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 118.1 billion yen ($1.5 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 112.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 22.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 252.5 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 442.1 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 186.4 billion yen in stocks, and sold 395.1 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 233.4
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  